Package edu.uky.cs.nil.sabre.comp

Interface CompiledEvent

All Superinterfaces:
Comparable<Logical>, Event, Logical, Serializable, Signed, Simplifiable, Unique
All Known Implementing Classes:
CompiledAction, CompiledTrigger
public interface CompiledEvent extends Event, Unique
A compiled event is a ground event which defines a unique ID number that corresponds to the event's index in its compiled problem's set of events, whose precondition is in disjunctive normal form, and whose effect is a clause.
Author:
Stephen G. Ware

    • getEffect

      default Clause<Effect> getEffect(Fluent fluent)
      Returns a clause composed of every effect in this event's effect that has the given fluent as its fluent. The returned clause may be empty if this event does not affect the given fluent, or it may have several atoms if this event has several conditional effects which might affect the given fluent.
      Parameters:
      fluent - the fluent which this event may affect
      Returns:
      a clause of all ways this event could affect the given fluent
